<div class="rebranding_container">
  <div class="text-image-block_wrapp block-flex-wrap block-gap-50 block-flex-center-sb">
    <div class="text-image-block_wrapp-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <h2 class="h2-heading-ss w-100">
        Louis Vuitton      
        <span class="h2-heading-pp">
          date codes
        </span>
      </h2>
      <p class="body-text">
        Louis Vuitton date codes are a crucial factor in authenticating Louis Vuitton bags. The date code is a combination of letters and numbers that indicate the manufacturing location and date of the bag. 
        <br><br>
        Typically, the date code is stamped on the interior tag or directly on the interior lining of the bag. To decode the date code, refer to the Louis Vuitton date code guide, which explains the meaning of the letters and numbers. 
        <br><br>
        For example, the first two letters represent the factory location, while the numbers indicate the week and year of production. Understanding these codes can help verify the authenticity of your Louis Vuitton bag.
      </p>
    </div>
    <img class="text-image-block_wrapp-image text-image-block_wrapp-image-small" src="{{ "lv_date-codes.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="Authentic Louis Vuitton date codes">
  </div>
</div>

